olive oil
1 Brown Onion
1 carrot
½ head cos lettuce
1 cucumber
1 tin chickpeas
1 packet ginger paste
1 packet Apricot Sauce
¼ cup water
30 g butter
1 drizzle white wine vinegar
8 Mini Flour Tortillas
1 bag mint
1 packet Crushed Roasted Cashews
½ packet garlic paste
1 sachet Mild North Indian Spice Blend

• Finely chop onion. Grate the carrot. Shred cos lettuce (see ingredients).
• Thinly slice cucumber into sticks. Drain and rinse chickpeas.

• In a large frying pan, heat a drizzle of olive oil over medium-high heat. Cook
chickpeas and onion, tossing, until softened, 4-5 minutes.
• Add another drizzle of olive oil along with the garlic paste, ginger paste,
and Mild North Indian spice blend. Stir to coat and cook until fragrant,
1-2 minutes.
• Reduce heat to medium, then add apricot sauce, the water and the butter,
stirring chickpeas to coat, 1-2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.

• Meanwhile, in a medium bowl, combine cos lettuce, carrot, a drizzle of
white wine vinegar and olive oil. Season and set aside.
• Microwave mini flourtortillas on a plate in 10 second bursts, until
warmed through.

• Pick mint leaves. Bring everything to the table to serve.
• Build your tacos by adding a helping of salad to a tortilla.
• Top with apricot-glazed chickpeas and cucumber. Tear over mint and garnish
with crushed roasted cashews. Enjoy!